nodes.text: Fen Teak was a Muun painter, whose portraits bore an unmistakable style, and who was considered brilliant by the Sith Lord Darth Zannah. By 980 BBY, Dark Jedi Set Harth had acquired several of Teak's portraits and set them for display in his mansion on the planet Nal Hutta.
Fen Teak was mentioned in the 2009 novel Darth Bane: Dynasty of Evil written by Drew Karpyshyn. Teak's gender was not established.
